		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Shiru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">(...) As for graphics, in the early days everyone used paper sheets and manual convertion into data, (...)</div><br />OMG O_O I would die with it!!!<br /><br />MML seems a bit unreadable for nowadays, witch makes me remember a low-priority project I have in mind, a language like MML, but more intuitive, fast to learn, and readable. Maybe I will post some ideas, if someone like it. I don't know if people nowadays would use it, hence the low-priority attribute. I think the syntax of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Music_Macro_Language#Modern_MML_2" class="postlink">Modern MML</a> is good, only needs some fastful-to-write constructs, and additional features maybe related to sampling.<br /><br />What do you think???

		

