	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />People like to use MML because it is a well established standart, in use for like 30 years, and there are many compilers around. I don't think a new music language will get a real use, because there aren't too many MML users around these days.<br /><br />Speaking of making graphics on paper sheets, I did that too, in mid 90s. It is kind of fun, just not very productive.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


