	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I did that when I was just started to learn programming and game development, it was around 1994. I used ZX Spectrum, and as I didn't have any graphics software, I created graphics on paper sheets.<br /><br />As I know, in pro development paper sheets were used till ~1985 for production graphics, and later they were mostly used for things like planning screen layouts and locations.

		

		</td>
